                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/3</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State to the Consul General at
                        Rotterdam</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LS1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Listoe</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-23">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Telegraph fully whether your office is transmitting commercial correspondence to
                    and from Germany or other country or whether arrangements being made to that
                    end. If so explain nature and number of telegrams, whether from Americans or
                    foreigners and authority for transmitting. Answer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
